2. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper proposes a new database search technique that can be used with homomorphic encryption. 
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the real-world ramifications of homomorphic encryption, which can have implications for privacy and security in society. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a new technique for secure database search, which can be considered a software engineering problem. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses a new technique for searching a database, which can be considered a data structures and algorithms problem.
